'''SAS ''Galeshewe''''' is a {{sclass2-|Warrior|strike craft|1}} of the [[South African Navy]], currently configured as an Offshore Patrol Vessel.
She was commissioned in 1983 and originally named SAS ''Hendrik Mentz'' for [[South African Party]] minister of defence [[Hendrik Mentz]], she was renamed on 1 April 1997.<ref name="Wessels">{{cite web | url=http://humanities.ufs.ac.za/dl/userfiles/Documents/00001/1095_eng.pdf | title=The South African Navy during the years of conflict in Southern Africa 1966-1989 | accessdate=August 14, 2014 | author=Wessels, Andre}}</ref> She was upgraded in 2012/2013 to an Offshore Patrol Vessel role.<ref name="DWEB10051023">{{cite web | url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=30430 | title=Navy commences upgrade of fourth strike craft | publisher=Defenceweb.co.za | date=10 May 2013 | accessdate=18 July 2014 | author=Wingrin, Dean}}</ref>
The SAS ''Galeshewe'' is currently employed with anti piracy patrols.<ref name="Dweb2013">{{cite web | url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=32682:opvs-take-up-counter-piracy-duties&catid=108:maritime-security | title=OPVs take up counter piracy duties | publisher=Defenceweb.co.za | date=November 14, 2013 | accessdate=December 8, 2014 | author=Helfrich, Kim}}</ref><ref name="DWebMartin">{{cite web | url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=31381:sas-isaac-dyobha-takes-over-from-sas-galeshewe-patrolling-mozambique-channel&catid=51:Sea&Itemid=106 | title=SAS Isaac Dyobha takes over from SAS Galeshewe patrolling Mozambique Channel | publisher=Defenceweb | date=July 30, 2013 | accessdate=December 9, 2014 | author=Martin, Guy}}</ref>
